Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: ModuleNotFoundError for matplotlib

pip3 install --user matplotlib pandas seaborn numpy
Issue: Permission denied when saving files

chmod 755 ~/security_viz_lab/outputs
Issue: Plots not displaying

Add plt.show() after plt.savefig()
Or use plt.savefig() only for headless environments
Issue: CSV file not found

# Verify file paths
ls -la ~/security_viz_lab/data/
# Use absolute paths in scripts if needed
Issue: Empty or malformed charts

Check data loaded correctly: print(df.head())
Verify column names match CSV headers
Ensure no null values: print(df.isnull().sum())
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated practical security data visualization using Matplotlib and Python. You learned to transform raw security telemetry into actionable visual insights through charts, graphs, and automated reports. These skills are essential for security analysts to communicate findings effectively and identify threat patterns quickly.

